  <section>
    <h2>Accessibility</h2>

    <h3>Decorative Icons</h3>
    <p>Icons that don't convey information should be hidden from assistive technology.</p>
    <code-block language="html" label="Decorative icon">{{ decorativeIconCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <h3>Informative Icons</h3>
    <p>Icons that convey meaning need accessible names.</p>
    <code-block language="html" label="Informative icons">{{ informativeIconCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <h3>Interactive Icons</h3>
    <p>Wrap icons in buttons or links with proper labels.</p>
    <code-block language="html" label="Interactive icons">{{ interactiveIconCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <h3>Best Practices</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Use <code>aria-hidden="true"</code> on decorative icons</li>
      <li>Provide <code>&lt;title&gt;</code> or <code>aria-label</code> for meaningful icons</li>
      <li>Don't rely on icons alone - pair with visible text when possible</li>
      <li>Ensure sufficient color contrast</li>
      <li>Test with screen readers</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Related Elements</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="/docs/elements/web-components/icons/"><code>&lt;icon-wc&gt;</code></a> - VB's icon component wraps SVG with sprite support and consistent sizing</li>
